==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[deinosaur]] ''(archaic)''

===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} '''[[δεινόσαυρος]]''' (''deinosauros''), from '''[[δεινός]]''' (''deinos'') "terrible, stiff, masterly, skilful" + '''[[σαύρα]]''' (''saura'') "lizard".

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''dinosaur''' (''plural:'' '''[[dinosaurs]]''')

# Any of various [[extinct]] [[reptile]]s existing between about 230 million and 65 million years ago.
#(''figurative, colloquial'') A person who is very old or has very old-fashioned views.

====Synonyms====
*(''person who is very old''): [[fossil]], [[old fart]]

